0. Lily: 'I will not take part in the new play.'
Lily refused to take part in the new play. 

1. My friend Tina:'Don't you ever tell anyone about my problems again!'
Tina warn me not tell anyone about her problems!

2. My manager:'It was your fault that we lost the Siemens contract.'
My manager balamed us for losting the Simens contract.

3. The art critic: 'Picasso was definitely the most exciting artist of the twentieth century.'
The art critc admited Picasso was the most exciting artist of the twentieth century.

4. The reporter: 'I'm terribly sorry about getting the Minister's name wrong.' 
The reporter apologised for getting the Minister's name wrong.'

5. The police officer: 'We believe that you have been making threatening phone calls.'
The police officer accused me in making threatening phone calls.

6. My friends: 'Come on - you can do the marathon with us. You're just as good as us.'
My friends suggested/encouraged me do the marathon with them. 

7. The team manager:'I feel terrible now about contradicting Julie in front of the team.'
The team manager regreted contradicting Julie in front of the team.

8. My wife: 'don't worry about the arrangements. They're all under control.'
My wife reassured me all are under control.

9. My mother: 'You had your tonsils taken out at the age of nine, remember?'
My mother remind me that my tonsils had taken out at the age of nine. 


